============================================================================
APPROACH (per ADR-010 §"Approach to sabotage" — direct-bogus-IUT variant)
============================================================================

Original sabotage script (scripts/sabotage-test.sh) uses an HTTP-500 stub
server bound to host loopback. On Linux Docker default network, the
TeamEngine container could not resolve `host.docker.internal` → SocketTimeout
on Step 6 → smoke pipeline aborted before any Core @Test ran. The stub
server approach requires either (a) `--add-host=host.docker.internal:host-gateway`
on docker run + 0.0.0.0 bind on stub, or (b) Docker network bridge.

Pragmatic fallback used here (per ADR-010 §"if stub-server proves
problematic, fall back to ..."): point smoke at a guaranteed-non-CSAPI URL
(`https://example.com/no-such-cs-api`). The IUT returns HTML; Core's
landing-page assertions FAIL on JSON content-type / link-to-conformance
expectations; SystemFeatures' depends-on=core cascade triggers SKIP.

  $ export SMOKE_IMAGE_TAG=ets-deduped:latest SMOKE_PORT=8082
  $ export SMOKE_IUT_URL="https://example.com/no-such-cs-api"
  $ bash scripts/smoke-test.sh

